WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:04.506
As we start this series, a church every community needs.

00:04.666 --> 00:07.289
I wanna talk about the word church.

00:08.251 --> 00:17.802
And I don't know if you've been in a conversation when the word church came up, but sometimes there can be a tension in the air or an awkwardness in the air.

00:17.922 --> 00:28.594
And it happens for me because I talk about church even more often because every time I'm at a party or every time I'm at a wedding, what happens is somebody says to me, what do you do?

00:28.962 --> 00:32.126
And I used to say, I'm a pastor, but now most people don't know what that means.

00:32.706 --> 00:34.468
And so then I started to say, well, I'm a minister.

00:34.508 --> 00:36.490
And then people said, well, how come you don't wear like a collar?

00:37.011 --> 00:40.014
And so now I often say, I work at a church.

00:40.655 --> 00:42.897
And it always comes up at the barbershop.

00:42.917 --> 00:46.281
And I always wonder if they're going to like tighten that cape just a little bit more, right?

00:46.962 --> 00:50.606
And you kind of get different responses when you talk about church.

00:51.307 --> 00:54.290
The first is there's a small percentage of people who feel guilt.

00:54.754 --> 00:56.736
They would say, oh, I used to go to church.

00:56.877 --> 00:58.238
I went to church as a kid.

00:58.538 --> 01:00.000
I haven't gone in a long time.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.163
That's a small percentage of people.

01:02.203 --> 01:10.513
A lot of people, when they hear the word church, they feel uncomfortable because they don't know a lot about it, or they're very skeptical about it.

01:10.533 --> 01:18.222
They've either heard stereotypes of church, or they've seen something in a movie, and they're feeling, oh, I don't know a lot about this.

01:18.462 --> 01:21.906
They know as much about church as some of you might know about attending a mosque,

01:22.082 --> 01:24.425
or a Hindu temple or a Harry Krishna service.

01:24.445 --> 01:26.548
They just, they don't really know what to say.

01:27.609 --> 01:33.596
Or when some people hear church, there's like a curiosity, it's kind of like a curiosity about a club that you belong to.

01:34.117 --> 01:39.644
Like, oh, I see some of them are like united and Baptist and are the Baptist not united?

01:39.704 --> 01:40.585
They're separate.

01:40.605 --> 01:41.606
No, no, it's like different.

01:41.987 --> 01:43.148
Like what is the club?

01:43.188 --> 01:45.491
And then they say like, I don't really belong to one.

01:45.571 --> 01:49.256
They see it more as a club, some kind of religious club.

01:50.598 --> 01:50.898
Now,

01:51.138 --> 01:56.643
with that awkwardness and the tension, it's very, very different when the word Jesus comes up.

01:56.663 --> 02:00.867
When you start talking about Jesus, it brings a curiosity in the air.

02:01.908 --> 02:04.171
People will say, I like Jesus.

02:05.352 --> 02:06.753
Like I like he was good to people.

02:06.793 --> 02:07.974
He said to love people.

02:08.034 --> 02:08.875
Like I like that.

02:08.915 --> 02:09.356
I like that.

02:09.636 --> 02:11.317
I'm interested in Jesus.

02:11.418 --> 02:13.780
But did he really die in a cross?

02:13.860 --> 02:15.281
Did he really rise again?

02:15.301 --> 02:17.523
Or I've read some of the Bible before.

02:17.604 --> 02:18.645
I've read about Jesus.

02:18.725 --> 02:20.146
Or I have a friend

02:20.226 --> 02:23.771
who found Jesus and their life is kind of being changed.

02:24.012 --> 02:30.241
And there's a curiosity, there's a warmth around Jesus when his name comes up.

02:30.261 --> 02:35.489
We all know people who are curious about Jesus, but they're a little uncertain about church.

02:35.669 --> 02:38.473
Now, why are people a little uncertain about church?

02:38.513 --> 02:41.017
Let me tell you one of the reasons, because they've been to one.

02:42.399 --> 02:44.502
And their experience at church was not a good one.

02:45.404 --> 02:49.650
And maybe that's you today, maybe you've arrived here and you've had past experiences that weren't good.

02:50.210 --> 03:04.506
that it's a club, it's a clique, they weren't welcome in any way, or somebody shared a message from the front, and it was in English, but you couldn't really understand it.

03:06.128 --> 03:18.962
They were saying stuff from the front, but they didn't really understand what they were saying, or they came and they said, well it was great, but it was like a two and a half hour service, and they sang a whole bunch of songs, I don't know any of the words too, and I was completely lost,

03:19.330 --> 03:23.976
or I didn't feel welcome or it had a moldy basement or whatever it might be.

03:24.377 --> 03:26.941
And they've had a poor experience in church.

03:27.902 --> 03:32.949
The other reason why people sometimes are awkward about church is because they've never been to one.

03:33.690 --> 03:36.193
So they think they wouldn't be welcome at one.

03:36.654 --> 03:38.156
Why would I be welcome at a church?

03:38.216 --> 03:39.979
Would they even have me?

03:39.999 --> 03:42.242
I don't have like a club card to get in.

03:42.302 --> 03:48.210
Like would I even be allowed to come to the church and would anybody even accept me there?

03:49.154 --> 03:56.683
But here's why we have to have this conversation about Jesus and about church, because you can't separate Jesus from the church.

03:56.863 --> 03:57.464
And here's why.

03:58.004 --> 04:00.167
He started the movement.

04:00.187 --> 04:02.009
Jesus started the movement of the church.

04:02.710 --> 04:08.056
To Jesus, the local church is his movement around the world.

04:08.957 --> 04:16.306
And that's what's amazing to me, that globally today, that all around the world, even in countries where they're persecuting Christians,

04:16.450 --> 04:24.482
People are gathering together in different ways, just like we're gathering to talk about God, to sing about God, to pray together.

04:24.522 --> 04:27.306
And it's a movement that's spreading all around the world.

04:27.466 --> 04:30.370
And I've preached in churches that meet in prisons.

04:30.451 --> 04:33.175
I've preached in ones that meet in shacks in the Caribbean.

04:33.535 --> 04:36.379
I've preached in some that met in community centers.

04:36.800 --> 04:39.464
I've even preached in a church that met in a movie theater.

04:39.544 --> 04:43.730
If you can imagine a church that would do that.

04:43.906 --> 04:50.432
For no matter where you go in the globe, the movement of the church is on the move.

04:51.033 --> 04:56.438
And I was in the lobby here this past week, and I'm just reminded of how amazing it is.

04:56.458 --> 04:58.159
Let me just give you one example.

04:58.179 --> 05:01.162
I'm standing there, and in one glimpse, what happens?

05:01.743 --> 05:11.072
I meet somebody who's 17, who says to me, I'm here, and I'm reading the Bible, and I'm asking questions, and I'm trying to discover who Jesus is.

05:11.572 --> 05:13.714
And then I meet a guy who's 75,

05:14.114 --> 05:20.621
And he says, I'm here, I'm reading the Bible, I got questions about faith, I'm trying to discover who Jesus is.

05:20.701 --> 05:23.003
Both all the generations are together.

05:23.043 --> 05:27.708
There are very few places in our world where all the generations come together at the same time.

05:28.689 --> 05:35.837
Another thing I love about the local church is the fact that there are people walking with the next generation at all ages and stages.

05:36.157 --> 05:41.042
Not just when they're teenagers, not just when they're middle schoolers, but all the way through.

05:41.122 --> 05:44.265
from preschool and infancy all the way to adulthood.

05:45.606 --> 05:47.008
We've been the benefit of that.

05:47.068 --> 05:48.109
I have two sons.

05:48.850 --> 05:52.914
And when we started this church, they were the only two kids in preschool at the early service.

05:53.874 --> 06:08.048
And they have had Gayle walk with them and Michael walk with them and Tyler walk with them and Emily walk with them, names of people that we know that have walked with them from the day that they were born all the way up through life.

06:08.248 --> 06:09.810
What other place does that?

06:10.370 --> 06:15.075
walks with an entire group of kids, entire family through all the generations.

06:15.095 --> 06:22.123
And then you've got the opportunity of spaces like Alpha for people to bring their questions and no question is off the table.

06:22.143 --> 06:30.412
And then at the same time, I was in a meeting this week where we're talking about how we could get behind the food bank and what we could do with local shelters and how we could help feed people.

06:30.692 --> 06:35.738
I mean, the local church as the movement of Jesus is a mutual fund of goodness.

06:37.540 --> 06:39.762
And it's an incredible thing to see.

06:40.610 --> 06:43.154
Only God could come up with something like this.

06:43.714 --> 06:47.660
And you can actually see when Jesus starts the movement.

06:48.081 --> 06:50.925
He's with Peter and they're having a conversation.

06:50.985 --> 06:53.368
And he says to Peter, who do you say I am Peter?

06:53.769 --> 06:55.351
And he says, well, you're the Messiah.

06:55.391 --> 06:56.232
You're the Son of God.

06:56.272 --> 06:57.995
You're the chosen one.

06:58.135 --> 06:59.657
And then this is what Jesus says.

07:00.018 --> 07:02.682
You did not learn this from any human being.

07:02.742 --> 07:04.364
This is a revelation to you.

07:05.706 --> 07:08.530
And now I say to you that you are Peter, which means

07:08.706 --> 07:11.430
Rock, and upon this rock, I will build my church.

07:11.450 --> 07:12.251
He doesn't mean Peter.

07:12.632 --> 07:18.500
He means this idea of profession of faith and who Jesus is and that you are the Messiah.

07:18.901 --> 07:21.605
Seeing people who have this revealed to them and confess it.

07:21.865 --> 07:26.672
I'm gonna build my church on this and all the powers of hell will not conquer it.

07:27.293 --> 07:32.521
And the actual word he uses here for churches, ecclesia, which is like a gathering with a purpose.

07:33.222 --> 07:35.986
It's a group of people who are gathered with the purpose.

07:36.386 --> 07:42.193
And there are all kinds of metaphors in the Bible that are used to describe the church.

07:43.334 --> 07:45.637
One of them is that the church is the bride of Christ.

07:45.837 --> 07:51.043
Jesus is like the groom, and we're like the bride, and he gives his life for us, and he lays down his life for us.

07:51.383 --> 07:58.772
But another metaphor that's used probably the most often and used a lot by Paul is the body.

07:59.613 --> 08:01.415
He says, we are the body of Christ.

08:02.216 --> 08:04.018
That when we gather together,

08:04.290 --> 08:06.152
We make up the body and he is the head.

08:06.172 --> 08:07.594
And so we all play a different part, right?

08:07.875 --> 08:13.262
Some people are the hand and some people are foot and some people are the arm and some people are the armpit, right?

08:13.342 --> 08:14.684
Who are the armpits here today?

08:14.944 --> 08:16.947
But we all have a different role to play.

08:16.987 --> 08:18.188
We all have a different part to play.

08:18.509 --> 08:23.656
And when we come together, we are the representation of Christ.

08:23.676 --> 08:26.039
You can't love Jesus without loving the church.

08:26.700 --> 08:27.100
You know that?

08:27.941 --> 08:31.506
That is clear that the church is his bride.

08:32.642 --> 08:34.304
And the church is his plan A.

08:34.364 --> 08:37.627
To Jesus, the church is his plan A for the planet.

08:39.209 --> 08:42.593
And to Jesus, the church is his plan A for Simcoe County.

08:44.355 --> 08:51.742
And that we are the representation of Jesus as we come together, as we gather together, as we're on mission together.

08:52.103 --> 08:54.285
That's why he calls us the body of Christ.

08:55.567 --> 08:59.110
So as the body of Christ, what should we look like?

08:59.411 --> 09:01.032
What should we look like as a church?

09:01.072 --> 09:02.514
Who should we be to our

09:02.722 --> 09:03.263
community.

09:04.444 --> 09:08.890
See, a church worth finding looks like the Jesus who found you.

09:09.971 --> 09:14.597
If you've been found by Jesus, a church worth finding looks like Jesus.

09:14.817 --> 09:16.820
We are the representation of Jesus.

09:16.860 --> 09:17.901
That's what we look like.

09:17.941 --> 09:21.285
And the honest truth is the church hasn't always gotten this right.

09:22.046 --> 09:27.753
That when you look back in the overall history of the church, sometimes the church has done this well and look like Jesus.

09:28.094 --> 09:31.378
And sometimes the church has done a lot of damage and a lot of harm.

09:32.322 --> 09:38.631
There's a book called Bullies and Saints by a guy named John Dixon, and it's all about the history of the church.

09:39.633 --> 09:42.878
And he looks at the overarching history, and he says this.

09:42.938 --> 09:45.441
He says, Christ wrote a beautiful tune.

09:45.502 --> 09:53.654
He had a great design for the church, a beautiful piece of music, which the church has often performed well and often badly.

09:54.615 --> 10:02.066
But the melody was never completely drowned out, and sometimes, sometimes it became a symphony.

10:03.106 --> 10:14.245
then when we look at how scripture has designed the movement of the church, and we look at what it means for us to look like the Jesus we represent, there's nothing like it.

10:15.106 --> 10:20.635
And it's his plan A for the globe, and it's his plan A for Simcoe County.

10:21.817 --> 10:29.330
And so if people are skeptical about church, or curious about church, or wondering about church,

10:29.986 --> 10:37.540
How can our church actually look more like Jesus if we represent Him as we gather and as we go about our lives?

10:37.560 --> 10:38.902
That's what this series is about.

10:39.623 --> 10:43.651
And what we're going to do is we're going to look at four aspects of Jesus.

10:44.132 --> 10:46.336
We're going to look at the personality of Jesus.

10:46.356 --> 10:46.837
That's today.

10:46.897 --> 10:49.441
We're going to look at the posture of Jesus.

10:49.962 --> 10:52.086
We're going to look at the purpose of Jesus.

10:52.467 --> 10:54.290
And we're going to look how we can have access

10:54.402 --> 10:55.703
to the power of Jesus.

10:55.743 --> 11:02.210
And as we do that, as a church, we can be a church that our community needs as we look like him.

11:02.270 --> 11:05.794
And so today, I wanna look at the personality of Jesus.

11:05.814 --> 11:12.360
Now, personality, if somebody said, what's your personality, it's how you consistently show up in people's lives.

11:12.921 --> 11:14.583
So if somebody said, hey, what's his personality?

11:14.603 --> 11:18.807
And I say, he's funny, that's because every time I hang out with that guy, he's funny.

11:19.448 --> 11:21.810
If I say his personality is he's boring,

11:22.338 --> 11:24.721
Every time I've hung out with that guy, he's often boring.

11:24.761 --> 11:27.104
It's how you consistently show up in someone's life.

11:27.485 --> 11:30.910
So how did Jesus consistently show up in people's lives?

11:31.290 --> 11:33.393
What was his personality?

11:34.474 --> 11:37.378
And that's what I want to look at for the rest of our time today.

11:38.500 --> 11:46.791
And there's an account in the Gospel of Luke where you really see the personality of Jesus shining through how he showed up for people.

11:47.512 --> 11:51.858
He is with a group of Pharisees who are religious leaders and they say, hey,

11:51.970 --> 11:53.432
We know how to live.

11:53.492 --> 11:54.413
We know the rules.

11:54.674 --> 11:56.596
We know how religion is supposed to be handled.

11:57.057 --> 11:58.659
And Jesus is blowing their minds.

11:59.320 --> 12:02.785
Because Jesus is hanging out with all the people he shouldn't.

12:03.426 --> 12:05.749
He's hanging out with tax collectors.

12:06.129 --> 12:07.371
And tax collectors, then we're bad.

12:07.391 --> 12:10.215
If you're a tax collector today, it's different, right?

12:10.255 --> 12:16.463
But tax collectors, prostitutes, people who were known to be of quote unquote ill repute.

12:16.844 --> 12:18.967
And they don't mind if Jesus teaches them.

12:19.407 --> 12:21.490
That's fine, Jesus, if you want to teach them, because you know what?

12:21.602 --> 12:22.803
They need to be taught.

12:24.585 --> 12:27.128
But what he's doing is he's hanging out with them.

12:27.148 --> 12:28.309
He's having dinner with them.

12:28.730 --> 12:29.811
He's inviting them over.

12:30.552 --> 12:32.855
And the Pharisees are like, you cannot do this.

12:33.135 --> 12:35.197
These people don't belong in our temple.

12:35.497 --> 12:37.059
They don't belong in our religion.

12:37.400 --> 12:40.303
They don't belong in our circle.

12:40.663 --> 12:41.985
And I don't want you.

12:42.085 --> 12:43.827
You shouldn't be spending any time with them.

12:45.228 --> 12:50.354
What happens is Jesus starts telling these stories that illustrate

12:50.594 --> 12:55.459
his personality and how he feels about the circumstance.

12:55.479 --> 12:59.944
And I want to share with you one of them that's one of the cornerstones of what this church was built on.

13:00.805 --> 13:05.030
It says this, to illustrate the point further, Jesus told them this story.

13:05.871 --> 13:12.619
A man had two sons and a younger son told his father, I want my share of your estate now before you die.

13:12.699 --> 13:13.900
I want my inheritance now.

13:13.920 --> 13:15.462
I know you're not dead.

13:15.622 --> 13:16.243
I wish you were.

13:16.303 --> 13:17.424
Can I have the cash?

13:18.886 --> 13:19.186
Right?

13:20.130 --> 13:22.934
And the Pharisees are already like, who is this jerk?

13:24.636 --> 13:27.400
So his father agreed to defy this wealth between his sons.

13:27.460 --> 13:32.767
And a few days later, this younger son packed all his belongings and moved to a distant land.

13:33.147 --> 13:36.191
Now, if you just move your kid away to school, this is triggering for you.

13:36.252 --> 13:37.433
I'm sorry, but it's not about that.

13:38.655 --> 13:40.958
Packed all his belongings and moved to a distant land.

13:41.178 --> 13:44.222
And there he wasted all his money in wild living.

13:44.703 --> 13:47.486
And the Pharisees are like, who is this kid?

13:48.408 --> 13:50.130
Who treats their dad like this?

13:50.914 --> 13:59.704
This is about the time his money ran out, a great famine swept over the land, and he began to starve, and the Pharisees are like, serves him right.

14:02.366 --> 14:07.392
And he persuaded a local farmer to hire him, and the man sent him into the fields to feed the pigs.

14:07.832 --> 14:14.239
So as a Jewish young man, now he's interacting with pork, which is terrible, and the Pharisees are like, this guy deserves it.

14:15.741 --> 14:20.306
It says, a young man became so hungry that even the pods he was feeding the pigs looked good to him,

14:20.930 --> 14:25.297
but no one gave him anything and the Pharisees are like, that's right.

14:25.797 --> 14:27.039
No one should give him anything.

14:29.282 --> 14:36.313
And when he finally came to his senses, he said to himself, at home, even the hired servants, they have food enough to spare.

14:36.593 --> 14:37.996
Here I am dying of hunger.

14:38.296 --> 14:39.838
I'm gonna go home to my father.

14:39.898 --> 14:43.844
I will go home to my father and say, Father, I've sinned against both heaven and you.

14:44.225 --> 14:46.208
I'm no longer worthy to be called your son.

14:46.628 --> 14:48.491
Please take me on as a hired servant.

14:48.651 --> 14:50.354
I'm gonna go back to my dad and say, listen,

14:50.786 --> 14:51.847
I'm going to learn a trade.

14:51.867 --> 14:53.470
I know I'm not allowed in the house.

14:53.670 --> 14:55.092
I know I'm not back in the family.

14:55.132 --> 15:00.880
Let me like work in the stable or be us blacksmith or something."

15:00.900 --> 15:02.702
So we returned home to his father.

15:04.344 --> 15:04.945
And this is this.

15:05.045 --> 15:10.994
And while he was still a long way off, his father saw him coming and the Pharisees are like, good.

15:12.355 --> 15:17.202
Now his dad is going to tell him, I told you so.

15:19.842 --> 15:29.476
And then Jesus says, and filled with love and compassion, he ran to his son, and he embraced him, and he kissed him.

15:31.739 --> 15:33.321
And the Pharisees are like, what now?

15:34.844 --> 15:35.464
He did what?

15:38.349 --> 15:44.978
This moment shows so clearly the personality of Jesus.

15:46.338 --> 15:49.901
that God's heart beats fast for those who are far from Him.

15:51.423 --> 15:53.145
And He runs towards their mess.

15:54.546 --> 16:05.517
And if you are here today and you think, man, my life is a mess, that's why I showed up here, I want you to know that Jesus has already been running towards you.

16:07.478 --> 16:09.140
It's what I love about our church.

16:10.201 --> 16:13.164
If you're here today and you're like, man, I barely got here.

16:13.304 --> 16:15.346
I am so hungover from last night.

16:16.034 --> 16:18.397
I want you to know you're not the only one.

16:23.042 --> 16:26.746
If you're here today and you're saying, man, I've got a secret sin.

16:27.246 --> 16:34.514
And if anybody found out and it's so heavy, you're not the only one.

16:37.778 --> 16:40.601
And if you're here and you say, man, I've made a lot of mistakes.

16:41.022 --> 16:42.203
I've messed up my marriage.

16:42.323 --> 16:43.585
I've messed up relationships.

16:43.685 --> 16:44.946
I've messed up parenting.

16:46.018 --> 16:47.119
You're not the only one.

16:49.001 --> 16:54.686
And Jesus says, I run towards your mess and my heart beats for you.

16:57.249 --> 17:00.152
I'm running toward you, not away from you.

17:02.434 --> 17:06.318
And it says, his son said to him, you can hear the son, he's got his speech prepared.

17:06.838 --> 17:10.942
Father, I have sinned against both heaven and you, and I'm no longer worthy of being called your son.

17:13.064 --> 17:14.866
And what's so interesting to me

17:14.946 --> 17:20.772
is what makes this confession so much easier is he already knows the Father loves him.

17:21.834 --> 17:26.378
It's not like he confesses his sin and the Father says, okay, you're sorry, I love you now.

17:26.639 --> 17:29.482
No, no, the Father loved him even before he confessed.

17:30.503 --> 17:32.405
Confession doesn't earn God's love.

17:32.445 --> 17:35.268
It's in response to God's love.

17:35.288 --> 17:37.471
He says, man, you've loved me so much.

17:38.151 --> 17:40.594
Of course I wanna confess my sin to you.

17:40.802 --> 17:41.924
You love me so much.

17:42.124 --> 17:44.487
Of course I want to lay this before you.

17:44.507 --> 17:46.230
Of course I want to be honest with you.

17:46.450 --> 17:48.112
Of course I want to be forgiven.

17:51.097 --> 17:57.285
It's just but his father said to his servants, quick, bring the finest robe in the house and put it on him and get a ring for his finger.

17:57.305 --> 18:03.134
It's and get sandals for his feet and kill the calf because we're going to have the most amazing barbecue.

18:03.174 --> 18:05.177
So he says, kill the calf we've been fattening.

18:05.477 --> 18:09.042
We must celebrate with the feast for this son of mine was dead.

18:09.122 --> 18:14.529
And he's now returned to life, he was lost, and now he is found, and so the party began.

18:14.589 --> 18:18.254
He doesn't just run towards him.

18:18.274 --> 18:20.117
I mean, just think about it.

18:20.157 --> 18:27.066
You know he had to be out there watching for him already, looking for him already, seeing him already.

18:27.366 --> 18:39.122
If you would say, I'm like this brother, and I'm broken, and I'm messed up, I want you to know, before you even got where you are today, God saw you, and he sees you, and he ran towards him.

18:39.362 --> 18:42.947
And he welcomes him home and he restores him to the family.

18:44.930 --> 18:47.093
And then he throws a party for him.

18:48.735 --> 18:49.516
See, this is the thing.

18:49.856 --> 18:56.426
This personality of Jesus shows us that the church isn't a club for the found, it's a search party for the lost.

18:59.289 --> 19:06.399
And I love it that I was here last week hanging out in the lobby and the last few weeks been praying for people.

19:06.439 --> 19:08.402
And when people come and they just

19:08.482 --> 19:09.483
They say, I'm a mess.

19:09.924 --> 19:12.947
I did this, and I did that, and I'm broken.

19:13.067 --> 19:14.349
And you know what?

19:14.569 --> 19:17.032
They're just like, I just need prayer.

19:17.112 --> 19:18.274
I need to know who God is.

19:18.434 --> 19:20.176
I'm desperate for God.

19:20.236 --> 19:21.478
I'm desperate to figure this out.

19:21.558 --> 19:22.779
Will you give me a Bible?

19:23.099 --> 19:25.522
I love that about our church.

19:26.804 --> 19:28.846
I love that we have space for that.

19:28.946 --> 19:30.448
I love that this place is for them.

19:30.468 --> 19:31.930
I love that I can say to them.

19:31.950 --> 19:35.314
They say, man, I'm so messed up, and I've got so many questions.

19:35.458 --> 19:38.762
And I can say to them, oh, that's really great because we built this church for you.

19:40.584 --> 19:41.625
But you're not the only one.

19:43.687 --> 19:46.170
That there are lots of us who are trying to figure all of this out.

19:48.332 --> 19:49.653
There's a guy named William Temple.

19:49.694 --> 19:52.156
He was the Archbishop of Canterbury in the mid 40s.

19:52.597 --> 19:53.358
And he has this quote.

19:53.398 --> 19:59.004
He says, the church is the only society that exists for the benefit of those who are not its members.

20:02.247 --> 20:04.850
And we can get so caught up, can't we?

20:05.186 --> 20:10.551
and saying, well, yeah, I know that's true, but like, how come they don't do this song more?

20:10.571 --> 20:12.333
Or how come they don't have more Bible study?

20:12.353 --> 20:13.615
Or how come they don't have more of this?

20:13.695 --> 20:15.296
And how come the church doesn't have more of that?

20:16.057 --> 20:17.118
And you know why that is?

20:17.418 --> 20:18.840
Because it's not always about you.

20:25.186 --> 20:32.754
The personality of Jesus is one who is broken, broken, and running towards the mess.

20:33.154 --> 20:45.830
and wrapping his arms around people and loving them in their brokenness in a place that they can be real and honest and confess and receive forgiveness because of his death on their cross and because of his resurrection.

20:48.393 --> 20:49.835
He didn't just run towards us.

20:49.915 --> 20:50.917
He died for us.

20:52.599 --> 21:01.490
And we want to be the kind of church, man, our gift to our community is to be a church that says, man, we want to wrap our arms around the mess.

21:02.530 --> 21:05.013
And people say, I'm not really sure about Jesus.

21:05.154 --> 21:05.514
Great.

21:05.834 --> 21:06.475
Come on in.

21:07.497 --> 21:08.498
I got a lot of questions.

21:08.698 --> 21:09.760
I got a lot to think through.

21:09.780 --> 21:10.240
I got a lot.

21:10.801 --> 21:11.342
That's great.

21:11.742 --> 21:15.968
We want to be the kind of church that welcomes the younger brother.

21:18.391 --> 21:19.373
But there's another brother.

21:21.015 --> 21:25.861
And the Pharisees already, like their jaws are on the ground.

21:26.502 --> 21:27.564
Like, you what?

21:27.784 --> 21:28.225
He what?

21:28.505 --> 21:29.266
He welcomed him.

21:29.486 --> 21:31.048
He didn't tell him I told you so.

21:31.609 --> 21:32.210
And then,

21:33.218 --> 21:34.760
Jesus pivots the story.

21:36.402 --> 21:39.125
And he says, oh, yeah, by the way, there's another brother.

21:41.208 --> 21:44.672
And he says, meanwhile, the older brother was in the fields working.

21:45.913 --> 21:49.998
And when he returned home, he heard music and dancing in the house, right?

21:50.639 --> 21:53.342
Here's that Tiesto in the house, right?

21:54.143 --> 21:55.565
He's like, that's my song, that's my song.

21:56.186 --> 21:56.787
What's going on?

21:59.009 --> 22:00.891
And it says, and he asks the servants, what's going on?

22:02.473 --> 22:02.994
And they say,

22:03.298 --> 22:03.999
Great news, man.

22:04.639 --> 22:05.621
Your brother is back.

22:06.481 --> 22:07.002
He was told.

22:07.362 --> 22:09.245
And your father has killed the fat and calf.

22:09.525 --> 22:11.487
It's like a dance and prime rib.

22:12.028 --> 22:14.410
And we're celebrating because of his safe return.

22:15.952 --> 22:20.697
We want to be that kind of church that celebrates when people come and discover Jesus.

22:21.358 --> 22:25.262
I mean, when they come in the door, we're not going to kill a calf and put them in the robe.

22:25.302 --> 22:26.203
That's weird.

22:26.243 --> 22:28.005
That's why people don't go to church.

22:28.085 --> 22:28.926
Weird stuff like that.

22:31.249 --> 22:32.530
But we're going to celebrate

22:35.554 --> 22:36.535
Your brother is back.

22:38.138 --> 22:42.505
And it said the older brother was angry and he wouldn't go in.

22:44.467 --> 22:47.973
And his father came out and he begged him.

22:48.093 --> 22:49.074
I want you to notice this.

22:50.196 --> 22:52.660
The father runs out of the house to both sons.

22:57.107 --> 23:04.658
He goes down the road to the younger son and he goes out to the field to the older son and he begged him.

23:08.514 --> 23:09.195
Come inside.

23:10.816 --> 23:11.657
Join the family.

23:13.639 --> 23:19.184
But he replied, Dad, all these years, Dad, I've slave for you.

23:19.204 --> 23:23.068
I never once refused to do a single thing you told me to.

23:23.108 --> 23:29.074
And in that time, you never gave me even one young goat for a feast with my friends.

23:32.077 --> 23:33.378
Look at all that I've done for you.

23:34.679 --> 23:35.460
I've been faithful.

23:36.561 --> 23:37.842
I've been showing up to church.

23:38.818 --> 23:56.704
doing the right things, living the right life, yet when catch this, yet when this son of yours, not my brother, this son of yours comes back after squandering your money on prostitutes.

23:57.085 --> 23:59.268
You celebrate by killing the fat and calf.

24:02.593 --> 24:03.314
Dad, I've been

24:03.778 --> 24:04.799
I've been doing my duty.

24:04.839 --> 24:05.640
I've been doing it right.

24:05.680 --> 24:10.266
I've been living the right life, making the right choices, doing all the right things.

24:12.189 --> 24:12.970
And you do what?

24:15.033 --> 24:19.659
And his father said to him, look, dear son, you've always stayed by me.

24:20.740 --> 24:22.362
And everything I have is yours.

24:25.206 --> 24:30.233
One of the things that he's inherited, of course, is he's going to have to take care of his younger brother probably for the rest of his life.

24:30.293 --> 24:31.314
This is going to cost him.

24:36.290 --> 24:42.377
What's interesting in this story is there are two lost brothers, aren't there?

24:43.738 --> 24:49.285
One brother lost in his rebellion, and one brother lost in the sin of self-righteousness.

24:53.450 --> 24:55.892
There's a book called Prodigal God by Tim Keller.

24:55.912 --> 25:00.297
It's a great book, and if I were to sum it up for you, one of the big points in the book is this.

25:00.397 --> 25:04.402
The younger brother was lost in his own badness, if you want to use that term.

25:05.442 --> 25:07.805
and the elder brother was lost in his own goodness.

25:10.869 --> 25:15.676
But both of them needed to father's love and grace the same.

25:22.345 --> 25:34.802
I think for all of us, if you call yourself a follower of Jesus today, we can have a lot of symptoms of older brotherliness in our lives.

25:37.154 --> 25:37.955
What does that look like?

25:37.975 --> 25:39.196
It can be superiority.

25:40.838 --> 25:51.928
You see someone who found Jesus, they lived a life and they made a whole mess and they found Jesus and you see their baptism video and you say, oh man, that's great for them.

25:53.330 --> 25:54.731
Man, they really needed Jesus.

25:58.074 --> 26:00.036
I'm really glad for them, they discovered God.

26:02.078 --> 26:06.322
But you know, it's been a number of years now and I got my walk of God together.

26:08.898 --> 26:13.545
Oh, that's for those people, but for me, I've kind of got it together.

26:13.605 --> 26:15.208
I kind of know how this all works.

26:18.693 --> 26:20.396
Or a sense of duty.

26:20.496 --> 26:24.542
I come to church every week and I bring my kids with me and I serve every week.

26:24.823 --> 26:26.566
Look at all the stuff I'm doing.

26:26.686 --> 26:28.308
I'm doing the duty.

26:30.592 --> 26:31.634
God owes me.

26:32.655 --> 26:34.037
I've done enough now that God owes me.

26:34.137 --> 26:34.919
I've got it together.

26:34.939 --> 26:37.042
There's a story about

26:37.314 --> 26:40.298
a guy who goes to a king and brings him a giant carrot.

26:40.318 --> 26:41.559
And I know you're like, where is this going?

26:41.579 --> 26:42.260
But stay with me.

26:44.323 --> 26:46.165
He brings a giant carrot to the king.

26:47.527 --> 26:49.850
And the king says to him, wow, you grew an amazing carrot.

26:50.510 --> 26:52.333
He says, I've got some land next to yours.

26:52.473 --> 26:55.256
I'm going to give it to you to grow a garden.

26:57.259 --> 26:58.621
Well, there's a guy standing there watching.

26:58.661 --> 27:00.543
He's like, wow, the king did that for a carrot.

27:01.885 --> 27:06.130
And the next day he shows up to the king and says, king, look, I brought you a stallion.

27:07.522 --> 27:09.425
And the king takes the stallion and gives him nothing.

27:10.868 --> 27:14.814
He's like, hey, you gave that guy a whole piece of land for a carrot.

27:14.874 --> 27:16.297
What are you gonna give me for a stallion?

27:16.497 --> 27:17.900
He says, you didn't give me the stallion.

27:17.940 --> 27:19.202
You gave yourself the stallion.

27:20.083 --> 27:22.888
You just gave it to me hoping I would give you something back.

27:25.753 --> 27:28.477
And I think a lot of us live our faith lives that way.

27:30.220 --> 27:31.082
A lot of you do.

27:32.104 --> 27:33.586
You think God owes you.

27:37.730 --> 27:38.952
because of your duty.

27:40.214 --> 27:41.195
I do the right things.

27:41.255 --> 27:42.377
I go through the right motions.

27:42.437 --> 27:43.278
I come on Sunday.

27:43.578 --> 27:44.380
I read the Bible.

27:44.980 --> 27:47.324
I'm sure God's keeping score and he owes me.

27:47.364 --> 27:48.045
He's good with me.

27:51.149 --> 27:53.192
Or for some of us, it's passivity.

27:54.714 --> 27:56.797
There's a passiveness to your faith.

28:00.343 --> 28:05.490
That you come on a Sunday and you would say, I've followed Jesus for 30 years.

28:06.722 --> 28:23.648
And I see you standing there with your arms folded during worship, with your coffee cup in your hand, with your mouth closed, passive, doing my duty, checking my chat box.

28:23.668 --> 28:25.030
That's older brotherliness.

28:26.132 --> 28:27.213
I've got it together.

28:28.615 --> 28:30.158
There's an exclusiveness to it.

28:30.498 --> 28:32.020
There's a judgmentalness to it.

28:32.241 --> 28:35.666
There's an element of I'm trying to control God with my behavior

28:35.746 --> 28:39.570
And under all of that sometimes is a real insecurity.

28:40.691 --> 28:46.356
I need to make sure that I've got a checklist and I'm following that because that makes me feel like I'm good with God.

28:49.299 --> 28:50.380
It's older brotherliness.

28:54.644 --> 29:00.309
And at the end of Luke 15, it says this next, we had to celebrate this happy day.

29:00.350 --> 29:03.713
The father says, for your brother was dead and has come back to life.

29:04.133 --> 29:05.074
He was lost.

29:05.218 --> 29:06.420
But now he is found.

29:07.962 --> 29:09.384
And that's the end of the story.

29:10.947 --> 29:12.689
The older brother doesn't come back in the house.

29:13.751 --> 29:15.573
The older brother doesn't return to the family.

29:19.219 --> 29:20.741
The other brother stays lost.

29:23.145 --> 29:23.806
That's what happens.

29:28.272 --> 29:34.802
I was here a few Sundays ago, and there was

29:34.978 --> 29:41.529
A young woman here who I watched in a service just over the corner of my eye.

29:43.372 --> 29:47.198
And she was just worshiping God with all her heart.

29:49.743 --> 29:58.597
And after words, I was talking to her and she said, a year ago I came here and I found Jesus at Alpha.

29:59.900 --> 30:01.362
And I want you to pray.

30:02.722 --> 30:08.890
that I would know more of the love of God in my life because I want more of it.

30:14.236 --> 30:29.435
And I think the thing that breaks my heart is there, some of you who have been Christians for five years, 10 years, 20 years, 30 years, and it's been a long time since you felt like that.

30:31.097 --> 30:31.698
Maybe ever.

30:35.170 --> 30:35.931
that you're lost.

30:38.514 --> 30:45.381
And you don't think you're lost because you've got your checklist and you come to church on Sunday and you serve and you read your Bible and you go, I'm not lost, I know what I'm doing.

30:46.402 --> 30:46.943
Do you though?

30:50.467 --> 30:52.829
Do you know the love of the Father in a real way?

30:54.791 --> 31:00.117
Do you know the love of a Father in a spiritual, supernatural way?

31:03.100 --> 31:04.722
And I think particularly,

31:05.250 --> 31:15.420
Guys, if this is you, particularly if you are a guy in this crowd and you feel that way, I have been praying for you all week.

31:15.440 --> 31:15.920
All week.

31:21.145 --> 31:33.116
I'm not asking you if you know whether Jesus died on the cross and rose again and God created the world and the Bible and all.

31:33.356 --> 31:35.218
I'm not asking you if you know it's true.

31:35.458 --> 31:38.020
I'm asking you if it's real to you.

31:42.665 --> 31:47.129
If you've got kids, I'll tell you a little secret about walking with your kids spiritually.

31:48.210 --> 31:51.754
When they're young, they want to know, they want you to tell them it's true.

31:52.715 --> 31:56.639
When they're older, they're watching to see if it's real to you.

31:59.081 --> 32:04.306
Is it?

32:05.474 --> 32:19.491
The reason my heart breaks for you is because the Father wants you to know His love, both brothers, the same.

32:22.214 --> 32:24.177
And you haven't known it for so long.

32:28.942 --> 32:33.508
And I know for some of you, in particular, guys, there's an element of life now.

32:33.528 --> 32:35.410
You know, my dad didn't show emotion

32:35.650 --> 32:40.134
I don't show emotion and I grew up whatever ethnicity you want to use as your excuse.

32:46.441 --> 32:49.824
When we say the church, the church isn't a club for the found.

32:49.944 --> 32:51.586
It's a search party for the lost.

32:53.247 --> 32:54.148
You're the lost too.

32:55.770 --> 32:56.311
You're lost.

33:03.117 --> 33:03.858
You know a lot.

33:06.338 --> 33:09.261
about Jesus, but you don't know the love of the Father.

33:12.725 --> 33:18.552
And I am begging you.

33:18.572 --> 33:23.958
I am begging you to open your heart just to crack.

33:27.221 --> 33:31.586
That the Holy Spirit might fill you and change you.

33:31.606 --> 33:35.090
That's something that's true to you, become something that's real to you.

33:39.330 --> 33:41.773
I know you're hearing my voice and you're like, I don't know.

33:41.873 --> 33:43.075
I'm having feelings.

33:43.375 --> 33:43.676
I know.

33:45.418 --> 33:46.340
I don't know what to do with this.

33:46.580 --> 33:46.880
I know.

33:48.923 --> 33:57.314
But would you be brave for your, for your own life, for your family, for your friends?

33:58.937 --> 34:07.108
Would you be brave enough to say, I'm gonna, I'm gonna go inside.

34:07.148 --> 34:08.850
I'm not gonna stay in the field anymore.

34:11.330 --> 34:13.333
Like what if the story had ended that way?

34:15.877 --> 34:18.641
Where both brothers had a party together with their dad.

34:21.506 --> 34:23.028
Because both of them had been found.

34:25.752 --> 34:31.722
And both of them were embraced by his love.

34:31.742 --> 34:33.044
He wants that for you.

34:36.469 --> 34:37.010
And so,

34:40.866 --> 34:44.089
ready today.

34:44.109 --> 34:45.231
It's been a weepy week.

34:52.158 --> 34:58.825
It's one second.

34:58.845 --> 35:06.614
If you're here and you're like, these tears just about this, yes, yes, this isn't anything else.

35:10.017 --> 35:10.578
If you

35:11.202 --> 35:12.284
are coming back to Jesus.

35:12.344 --> 35:19.275
If you're coming to Jesus today and you're the rebellious son and you're running back and you're saying, man, I've made a lot of messes.

35:20.036 --> 35:21.579
I've got addictions.

35:21.919 --> 35:23.001
I mess with my family.

35:23.301 --> 35:25.244
I mess with my job, whatever it is.

35:25.625 --> 35:32.396
I'm telling you, the father embraces you like the younger son and he already sees you and he's already running towards you.

35:32.676 --> 35:34.579
He's just waiting for you to run towards him.

35:35.240 --> 35:38.706
And as I pray today, if you want to choose to run back to Jesus,

35:39.330 --> 35:43.176
I encourage you to pray with me today and put your hand out on your lap as I pray.

35:44.057 --> 36:04.610
And if you're here today and you are the older brother, and I know some of you, some of you guys are already like, if he tells me to put my hand out on my lap, like I am not doing that, have courage enough.

36:04.630 --> 36:05.992
What if my wife sees good?

36:06.813 --> 36:07.154
Good.

36:09.250 --> 36:23.628
have courage enough to say, God, I'm open in my heart of crack, to know the Father's love, that I might know that what I know is true is here, that I might go on a journey to discover that it's real here.

36:28.594 --> 36:34.861
Because you've been a Christian for a long time, but there are people here who've been Christians for less than a year, and they know more about that than you.

36:37.945 --> 36:38.706
Believe that.

36:41.890 --> 36:43.733
but it doesn't mean it isn't for you.

36:45.175 --> 36:46.176
It totally is.

36:48.179 --> 36:56.231
The Father sees you and he loves you and he says, come in from the field and let me wrap my arms around you and let's celebrate together.

36:58.575 --> 37:02.360
So if you wanna put your hand out on your lap while I pray, I'm gonna get people to close their eyes.

37:02.501 --> 37:03.222
It's gonna be fine.

37:05.405 --> 37:08.850
Just close our eyes and you can pray with me.

37:10.594 --> 37:13.858
Maybe for you, you're the younger brother, you're saying, God, I'm running back to you.

37:14.159 --> 37:15.140
I've made a mess.

37:15.801 --> 37:22.850
I'm done wandering around, making a mess, trying to just make more messes, trying to figure out life.

37:22.931 --> 37:24.413
And I run towards you.

37:29.780 --> 37:31.182
And I ask your forgiveness.

37:32.183 --> 37:34.146
And I confess to you, my sin.

37:35.507 --> 37:37.490
And I come to you for repentance.

37:37.794 --> 37:43.160
knowing that you wrap your arms around me and I'm responding to that love with repentance and confession.

37:45.623 --> 37:56.255
And if you're here and you're the older brother, God, I pray that as I open my heart a crack that you would fill me with the power of your spirit, that I might know your love in a real way.

37:58.457 --> 38:06.066
God, I give you permission to keep prime this crack open, that I might know the love of a father that never fails.

38:10.626 --> 38:15.192
God, I confess to you of my older brotherliness.

38:17.234 --> 38:19.377
And I want you to wrap your arms around me too.

38:22.501 --> 38:24.483
I want to know your love in a real way.

38:26.466 --> 38:31.852
Not something that's true, but also something that's real for me.

38:35.337 --> 38:36.338
And I pray this in your name.

